---
import LessonLayout from '../../layouts/LessonLayout.astro';
---
<LessonLayout
  title="Giving Instructions"
  track="little-explorers"
  week={3}
  phase="Phase 1: Unplugged"
  duration="30 min"
  emoji="📣"
  objective="Learn that robots need clear, step-by-step instructions"
>
  <section class="lesson-section mb-8">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-explorer-700 mb-3">🎯 Learning Objective</h2>
    <p class="bg-explorer-50 border-l-4 border-explorer-400 p-4 rounded-r-xl text-gray-700">
      Your child will experience why instructions must be specific and in the right order — and laugh at what happens when they're not!
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="lesson-section mb-8">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-800 mb-3">🛠️ Materials</h2>
    <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
      <li class="flex items-center gap-2">✅ A simple snack to "program" making (e.g., peanut butter on crackers)</li>
      <li class="flex items-center gap-2">✅ Index cards or sticky notes</li>
      <li class="flex items-center gap-2">✅ Crayons to draw the steps</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="lesson-section mb-8">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-800 mb-3">📋 Activity Steps</h2>
    <div class="space-y-4">
      <div class="flex gap-4 items-start">
        <span class="w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-explorer-500 text-white font-bold flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">1</span>
        <div><h3 class="font-bold">The Silly Robot (10 min)</h3><p class="text-gray-600">Parent plays a VERY literal robot. Child instructs how to make the snack. Follow instructions exactly as given — if they say "put peanut butter on it" and don't say "open the jar," pretend to put the closed jar on the cracker. Laugh and try again with better instructions.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="flex gap-4 items-start">
        <span class="w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-explorer-500 text-white font-bold flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">2</span>
        <div><h3 class="font-bold">Draw the Steps (10 min)</h3><p class="text-gray-600">Together, draw each step on a card. Put them in order. Number them 1, 2, 3... Can you follow the picture-cards exactly?</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="flex gap-4 items-start">
        <span class="w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-explorer-500 text-white font-bold flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">3</span>
        <div><h3 class="font-bold">Eat the Result! (5 min)</h3><p class="text-gray-600">Follow the final instruction set perfectly and enjoy the snack together. 🎉</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="flex gap-4 items-start">
        <span class="w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-explorer-500 text-white font-bold flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">4</span>
        <div><h3 class="font-bold">Reflect (5 min)</h3><p class="text-gray-600">Talk about how the instruction cards are like a "program" — just like what we'll give Reachy Mini later!</p></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="lesson-section mb-8">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-800 mb-3">💬 Reflection Questions</h2>
    <div class="space-y-3">
      <div class="bg-yellow-50 border border-yellow-200 rounded-xl p-4"><p class="font-semibold text-yellow-800">🌟 "What was the funniest mistake the robot made?"</p></div>
      <div class="bg-yellow-50 border border-yellow-200 rounded-xl p-4"><p class="font-semibold text-yellow-800">🌟 "Why does the order of steps matter?"</p></div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="lesson-section mb-8">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-800 mb-3">👪 Parent Tips</h2>
    <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-xl p-5 text-gray-700">
      <p>💡 The "silly robot" game secretly teaches <strong>algorithmic thinking</strong> — be as literal as possible for maximum laughs and learning.</p>
      <p class="mt-2">💡 Save the picture-step cards! In Week 4 we reference them when we meet Reachy for real.</p>
    </div>
  </section>
</LessonLayout>
